    "created_at": "2019-08-20T18:42:50Z",
    "updated_at": "2019-08-20T18:42:50Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "There's a bit of guidance in the fork choice document:\r\n\r\n> The large `ETH1_FOLLOW_DISTANCE` specified in the honest validator document should ensure that `state.latest_eth1_data` of the canonical Ethereum 2.0 chain remains consistent with the canonical Ethereum 1.0 chain. If not, emergency manual intervention will be required.\r\n\r\nMy suggestion would be to clear data (blocks, attestations, etc.) that is a certain age (e.g. 3 days) relative to the latest finalised checkpoint. We don't expect the latest finalised checkpoint to get reverted but keeping a bit of data around for emergency manual intervention may be worthwhile.",
