    "created_at": "2019-08-21T16:58:38Z",
    "updated_at": "2019-08-21T16:58:38Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The expectation of clients to start is to serve beacon blocks within the weak subjectivity period (~8M in the normal case) to allow for offline clients to sync to the head. Actively clearing out the store in your active fork choice alg after finality is certainly advisable, but pruning your blocks/state should be done in a much more conservative manner",
